1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:09,252
First, you do a warm-up: Use a blank spreadsheet.

3
00:00:09,252 --> 00:00:13,179
You point to a column letter, a row number and a cell.

4
00:00:13,179 --> 00:00:17,730
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:24,782
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Click A1, B1, A2 and C3.

6
00:00:24,782 --> 00:00:28,858
Use the name box or staff prompts to confirm each cell.

7
00:00:28,858 --> 00:00:35,149
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the name of the first top-left cell.

8
00:00:35,149 --> 00:00:42,364
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Ask what C2 means: column C, row 2.

9
00:00:42,364 --> 00:00:46,222
Use pointing if spoken explanation is difficult.

10
00:00:46,222 --> 00:00:48,773
Take one activity at a time.

11
00:00:48,773 --> 00:00:53,315
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

